                            <comment id="14376937" author="steve_rowe" created="Mon, 23 Mar 2015 23:50:45 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The &lt;tt&gt;&amp;#95;text&lt;/tt&gt; field and the copyField directive targetting it were added in &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-6471&quot; title=&quot;schemaless example should have catchall field&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SOLR-6471&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SOLR-6471&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14383075" author="yseeley@gmail.com" created="Fri, 27 Mar 2015 00:38:00 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Anyone have thoughts on changing&lt;br/&gt;
&quot;&amp;#95;text&quot; to either &quot;&amp;#95;text&amp;#95;&quot; or just &quot;text&quot;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14384359" author="erickerickson" created="Fri, 27 Mar 2015 18:48:21 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Personally I&apos;d slightly prefer &quot;&lt;em&gt;text&lt;/em&gt;&quot; to just &quot;text&quot;, although I can argue either way. &quot;&lt;em&gt;text&lt;/em&gt;&quot; is clearly a reserved field, OTOH &quot;text&quot; is something we already use as the df.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&quot;_text&quot; is a distant third IMO since it&apos;s too easy to confuse with a dynamic field.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;FWIW,&lt;br/&gt;
Erick&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14385473" author="ehatcher" created="Sat, 28 Mar 2015 19:00:23 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I prefer &amp;#95;text&amp;#95;.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14385657" author="varunthacker" created="Sun, 29 Mar 2015 07:15:47 +0000"  >&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;I prefer &amp;#95;text&amp;#95;.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;+1&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14395272" author="steve_rowe" created="Fri, 3 Apr 2015 23:36:14 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;+1 for &lt;tt&gt;&amp;#95;text&amp;#95;&lt;/tt&gt; - any objections to changing this in 5.1?  If we&apos;re going to change it, I think we should do it sooner rather than later.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14395279" author="yseeley@gmail.com" created="Fri, 3 Apr 2015 23:43:08 +0000"  >&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;+1 for &lt;em&gt;text&lt;/em&gt; - any objections to changing this in 5.1? If we&apos;re going to change it, I think we should do it sooner rather than later.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;+1&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14395280" author="erickerickson" created="Fri, 3 Apr 2015 23:45:41 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;+1 for changingin 5.1&lt;/p&gt;
</comment>
